# 🚀 Day 2 – Product Thinking & Metrics

## 🎯 Objective
Understand how to define Core Value, North Star Metric (NSM), and Supporting Metrics for different businesses.

---

## 🟡 Zomato

### 🔹 Core Value
Enable users to discover a variety of food options and get them delivered quickly and reliably.

### 🔹 North Star Metric (NSM)
Number of successful orders delivered.

### 🔹 Supporting Metrics
- Delivery time  
- Order success rate  
- Customer retention  
- Average order value  

---

## 🟣 Netflix

### 🔹 Core Value
Provide on-demand, personalized entertainment to users.

### 🔹 North Star Metric (NSM)
Total watch time (hours watched).

### 🔹 Supporting Metrics
- Daily Active Users (DAU)  
- Retention rate  
- Content completion rate  
- Subscription renewal rate  

---

## 🟢 Uber

### 🔹 Core Value
Enable users to get rides quickly, reliably, and affordably.

### 🔹 North Star Metric (NSM)
Number of completed rides.

### 🔹 Supporting Metrics
- Driver availability  
- Ride acceptance rate  
- Average wait time  
- Customer ratings  

---

## 🧠 Business Case: Amazon

### Problem
Revenue increased, but customer satisfaction decreased.

### Interpretation
Short-term growth but long-term risk due to declining user experience.

### Possible Reasons
- Delayed deliveries  
- Poor product quality  
- Pricing mismatch  
- Inefficient return process  

### Analysis Approach
- Customer ratings and reviews  
- Return rates  
- Delivery performance  
- Repeat purchase behavior  
- Seller performance  

### Recommendations
- Improve quality control  
- Optimize delivery operations  
- Enhance return experience  
- Monitor seller performance  

---

## 🚀 Key Learnings
- NSM should reflect customer value, not just revenue  
- Supporting metrics help diagnose problems  
- Short-term gains can harm long-term growth  
- Business thinking is critical in data analysis  

